  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) is amending its risk-based capital guidelines for state member banks and bank holding companies (banking organizations) to implement section 350 of the Riegle Community Development and Regulatory Improvement Act of 1994 (Riegle Act). Section 350 states that the amount of risk-based capital required to be maintained by any insured depository institution, with respect to assets transferred with recourse, may not exceed the maximum amount",
